                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>\n                <addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir, I have you<lb/> annexed, statement of collections<lb/>\n                made on a/c Occident, as well as<lb/> sales of Book's since last report<lb/>\n                together amounting to Fifty 35/00. Dols<lb/> for which I hand you enclosed<lb/> my\n                check on Mechanics Bank<lb/>\n                <placeName>New York</placeName> less Exchange 25c for Fifty<lb/> 10/00 Dolls. I am\n                pleased to learn<lb/> of the great progress you have made<lb/> in the Bibles\n                completion. I have<lb/> no doubt it will prove the means<lb/> of amply repaying you\n                for all your<lb/> labors bestowed in the publishing<lb/> way. Many Christians are\n                anxious<lb/> to see the work, &amp; I have no a number<lb/> will be sold to\n                them.</p>\n            <p>We have had two discourses<lb/> delivered in our Synagogue by<lb/> our <persName>Rev\n                    Mr. Jacobs</persName> in behalf of <del>our</del><lb/> suffering humanly in\n                    <placeName>New Orleans</placeName><lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. Jacobs</persName> was the first Minis<lb/>ter in our city who\n                suggested</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ws8j648/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
